<DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
   <title> The flex-direction Property </title>
   <style type="text/css">
      .container {
         display: flex;
         flex-direction: row;
         background: blue;
         padding: 10px;
      }
      .container > div {
         background: yellow;
         width: 100px;
         height: 100px;
         margin: 5px;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <div class="container">
      <div> 1 </div>
      <div> 2 </div>
      <div> 3 </div>
   </div>
   <p> <b>flex-direction</b> valid values: </p>
   <ul>
      <li><b>row</b>: the flex items run along from left to right in <code>ltr</code>; right to left in <code>rtl</code></li>
      <li><b>row-reverse</b>: the flex items run along from right to left in <code>ltr</code>; left to right in <code>rtl</code></li>
      <li><b>column</b>: the flex items run along from top to bottom </li>
      <li><b>column-reverse</b>: the flex items run along from bottom to top </li>
   </ul>
</body>
</html>